United STATES of America ex rel. Salvatore BOUCINO, Relator-Appellant, v. Edward CORSI, Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of New York, Respondent-Appellee. No. 402. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit April 17, 1933. Isaac Allen, of New York City, for appellant. George Z. Medalie, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Maurice De Koven, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges-

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
